# Completion Reporting

When a milestone or task requires a completion report, include **all** of the following sections.

## Required sections

### Summary
What was delivered and why, in a few sentences.

### Files Created
Bullet list of new paths.

### Files Modified
Bullet list of changed paths (or “None”).

### Tests Executed
Commands run and outcome, or “None (documentation-only)”.

### Migration Impact
Alembic/schema effects. Use **None** when no migrations were added or changed.

### Architecture Compliance
Confirm layering and especially **curriculum V1/V2** invariants. State whether traversal/import compatibility was preserved or N/A.

### Technical Debt
Honest leftover risk or follow-ups introduced by this work (or “None”).

### Known Limitations
Boundaries of what this milestone did not solve.

## Rules

- Be specific to Kwalitec — no placeholder lorem.
- Call out if application code was intentionally untouched.
- Include the commit hash when the milestone requires a commit.
- After the mandated commit/stop instruction, do not start the next milestone.
